    "Article-72 variant: origin country NO (Norway, a non-Article-72 country) combined with commodity code 0603197090 (an Article-72 commodity). No Article-72-specific question, page or interstitial rendered in this trace — the combination flows through the standard wizard unchanged, and the only assertion on the outcome is the CHED status tag in the BIP decision service. Whatever Article-72 rule exists is applied server-side and is NOT visible as a user-facing page in this journey.",
    "Zero errors in this trace, so it yields no validation/error copy.",
    "Page title vs visible heading diverge on the origin page: <title> is the generic 'Origin of the animal or product' (shared across all four CHED types) while the h1 is CHED-PP-specific: 'Origin of the plants, plant product or other objects'. pageGuess uses the h1. This generic-title/specific-h1 split is a sign of shared cross-CHED templates in IPAFFS.",
    "consignment/page-2 (reference number) was submitted empty — the consignment local reference is optional.",
    "responsible-person/contact-details (action 49) and nominated-contact (action 50) were both submitted with NO input. Their fields are presumably pre-populated from the signed-in user. These two pages are therefore UNCOVERED by this trace — their required fields are not evidenced here and must be corroborated against templates/page objects.",
    "Commodity details were set via the bulk-edit path (Select all -> fill -> Apply) at /commodity/details/bulk, not per-commodity. The per-commodity details page is uncovered by this trace.",
    "Commodity selection is a three-step chain: input-method (Manual entry) -> page-3 commodity code search -> page-4 'Select species of commodity' (the Add button). Searching (action 18) itself navigates to page-4 carrying ?commodity-selected-code=0603197090.",
    "'Same as consignee' (action 73) is a BUTTON, not a checkbox — it copies consignee details into the importer and reloads /traders.",
    "The document attachment is uploaded on a SEPARATE service path (/upload/vnet/protected/upload/...), then returns to documents/page-1 — a cross-service hop mid-journey.",
    "The trailing test-side POSTs to /ad/sign and /soapsearch/vnet/sanco/traces_ws/searchCertificate verify the notification reached the TRACES SOAP endpoint. Infrastructure/integration detail, not a user-facing requirement.",
    "Journey spans three distinct IPAFFS services on one host: /notification (the wizard), /upload (attachments) and /decision (BIP assessment)."
